<BODY>
<HEADLINE> August First Beaten, Eagles Flying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Reigning champions August
First's seven-win streak snapped, while Air Force Eagles gained
their first victory of the season in the Chinese basketball league
eight-round matches on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
August First conceded their first defeat in Nanjing, Jiangsu
province, to Jiangsu Dragons 83-80, while the Eagles trounced
Guangdong Tigers 77-66 to end up their seven staight loss streak
in the season.
</P>
<P>
Hu Weidong, the Best Scorer last season, sunk a free-throw 17
seconds from the time when the score dead-tied at 80-80, and
sealed Dragons the first ever victory over the superpower August
First.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhizhi led the game with 30 points, but failed to save his
team from the defeat of the season and the fourth in the
two-year-old league.
</P>
<P>
At Shi Jinshan Gymnasium in Beijing, Liu Degang was the biggest
gun with 26 points, followed by Liu Tie, 22 points, for Eagles.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Flaming Bulls ranks first on the standings with 16
points from eight games after they demolished Shanghai Oriental
72-62.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai got to a good start as they led in the first 10
minutes with 23-13, but almost squandered all their advantage
before the break and ended the first half 33-32.
</P>
<P>
Flaming Bulls overpowered their opponents five minutes into the
second half at 44-43 and led the score for good.
</P>
<P>
In Nanjing, Jiangsu province, Jiangsu Dragons needed two
overtimes to edg Beijing Ducks 89-86 in a cliff-hanger.
</P>
<P>
Mike King shot the winning three-pointer with just five seconds
from the final buzz before a 86-86 deadlock.
</P>
<P>
In the roller-roaster clash, Dragons quickly moved into the
game and led to finish the first half at 44-35, but could not hold
on their edge and ended the regular time at 72-all.
</P>
<P>
In the other Wednesday's matches, Liaoning Hunters routed
Shenyang Army Lions 76-66, while Sichuan Pandas beat Jinan Pegasus
86-80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
