<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-German Stainless Steel Plant to Be Built in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Pudong Iron and
Steel Group Company has signed a contract with Germany's Krupp &AMP;
Thyssen to jointly build a stainless steel plant in the Pudong New
Area in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of more than 1.4 billion U.S. dollars, the Shanghai
Krupp &AMP; Thyssen Stainless Steel Company is believed to be the
largest facilities of its kind in China. The German company will
fund 60 percent of the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
With imported smelting and hot- and cold-rolling technologies,
the joint venture is expected to produce 440,000 tons of stainless
steel a year.
</P>
<P>
China now has an increasing demand for stainless steel products
and consumes nearly 800,000 tons of stainless steel annually, more
than 400,000 tons of which are imported from abroad.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Pudong company has an annual production capacity
of 2.5 million tons of steel and 2.1 million tons of rolled
steel. It is one of the country's largest stainless steel makers
and one major producer of steel plates used for ship building.
</P>
<P>
Krupp and Thyssen produces 1.2 million tons of stainless steel
a year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
