<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Opens 10 More Peaks for Climbing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali Ministry of
Tourism and Civil Aviation has opened 10 more peaks for climbing,
said a press release issued today by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The newly opened peaks are Mt.Naya Khanka (5,863m.) and
Mt.Yala (5,732m.) in the central Rasuwa district, Mt.Chhukungri
(5,550m.) and Mt. Gokyori (6,850m.) in the eastern Solukhumbu
district, Mt.Rambrong (4,499m.) in the western Lamjung
district, Mt.Dama (6,855m.), Mt.Ramchaur (4,500m.),
Mt.Ramtang (6,601m.) and Mt.Tengkoma (6,215m.) in the eastern
Taplejung district and Mt.Kangtokla (6,294m.) in Dolpa district
of mid-western Nepal, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The royalty and other provisions on climbing these peaks will
be based on the existing rules and regulations, said the press
release.
</P>
<P>
The ministry hopes that the newly opened peaks will attract
additional mountaineers, the press release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
