<HEADLINE> First International Air Route for Southwest China Scenic City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Guilin City in southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region opened an air route to
the city of Fukuoka in Japan on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first international air route for the scenic city
of Guilin. The China Southern Airlines will operate chartered
flights on the route.
</P>
<P>
As of March 29 of next year, regular flights will be launched
every Tuesday and Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that another international air route, between
Guilin and Seoul, will open early next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
