<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial: Promoting Partnership of Good Neighborliness, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- An editorial, to be carried by
China's leading newspaper People's Daily on Thursday, hails the
just-concluded ASEAN-China-Japan-South Korea and China-ASEAN
informal leaders' meeting in Kuala Lumpur as a complete success.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin attended the two meetings held on
Monday and Tuesday respectively. It was another diplomatic move
taken by Jiang following his recent visits to the United States,
Canada and Mexico, said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
During the two meetings, 12 heads of states in East Asia looked
into the prospects of regional development, discussed regional
economic cooperation, and reached broad consensus on strengthening
good-neighborly friendship among East Asian countries, broadening
mutual-beneficial cooperation and promoting common development.
</P>
<P>
During the China-ASEAN meeting, President Jiang exchanged
in-depth views with ASEAN leaders on the development of the
China-ASEAN friendly cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
All the participants of the meeting agreed to establish a
partnership of good-neighborliness and mutual trust oriented to
the 21st century, and issued a joint statement in this regard,
said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that the holding of two meetings at the turn
of the century was a great pioneering work in the history of
development in the East Asia. It was of profound significance to
the future development of the East Asia and the China-ASEAN
friendly cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Viewed from the aspects of politics, economy, culture and
geopolitics, East Asia is a force which should not to be ignored
in today's international arena, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
Under the new circumstance of world multipolarization and
closer links between world economies, East Asian nations
surmounted all kinds of obstacles and difficulties through
development and mutual cooperation, said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
With the wealth of experience they accumulated, East Asian
nations will set an example of smooth economic cooperation for
other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
They will also play an increasingly important role in promoting
the establishment of a new international political and economic
order of peace, stability and justice, said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
China's economy has a direct bearing on the development of East
Asian nations. China offers numerous trade opportunities and a
large market for the region.
</P>
<P>
In return, the editorial said, the sustained and stable
economic development in East Asia is crucial for China's
development.
</P>
<P>
Having the region's prosperity and stability in mind, China
stressed that cooperation between East Asian nations should base
upon the principles of mutual respect, equal participation, mutual
benefit and common development, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
China always maintains that to guarantee a regional peace,
countries should seek common interests and iron out differences
through dialogue and consultations.
</P>
<P>
China will, as always, strengthen good-neighborly relations
with other East Asian countries and promote reciprocal
cooperation, the editorial stressed.
</P>
<P>
China and ASEAN are both important forces in maintaining peace
and stability and promoting cooperation and development.
</P>
<P>
China has made remarkable progress in its relations with ASEAN
and ASEAN members over the past decade, and notably so since they
established a comprehensive dialogue partnership. China and ASEAN
have been building up mutual confidence and strengthening their
cooperation in safeguarding peace and promoting development, said
the editorial.
</P>
<P>
China and ASEAN have both agreed to build a 21st
Century-oriented partnership and had the commitment written into
the Joint Statement.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that Both sides have decided to make full
use of the dialogue mechanism to coordinate with and support each
other on significant regional and global issues, and to safeguard
the justified interests and rights of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
They will continue to seek common ground and iron out their
differences and disputes through friendly consultations. China and
all the ASEAN members will be good neighbors, good partners and
good friends forever, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
To develop a trusting good-neighborlyness with ASEAN countries
is an important part of China's foreign policy, said the
editorial. "Even if China becomes developed in the future, it will
treat all countries as equal, will build its relations with all
countries on the basis of the five principles of peaceful
co-existence and will never seek hegemony. This stand has won high
praise from leaders of the ASEAN countries", the editorial added.
</P>
<P>
In all, the ASEAN-China-Japan-South Korea informal leader's
meetings have opened a new chapter in cooperation between East
Asian countries and between China and ASEAN. They reflect the new
trend of the world towards multipolarity, further embody the Asian
countries' common will to work together for regional peace and
development, and represent a new stage of the development of ties
between China and ASEAN countries, said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
"We can believe that through our joint endeavors and unremitting
efforts, China-ASEAN cooperation will be further strengthened in
the 21st century. The good-neighborly and mutually trusting
partnership between China and ASEAN will further develop on a new,
higher level", the editorial said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
