<HEADLINE> German Schoolgirl Murderer Receives Life Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A German young man who bludgeoned
a seven-year-old schoolgirl to death after sexually abusing her,
was Wednesday sentenced to life imprisonment in the southern
German city of Augsburg.
</P>
<P>
The court also deprived Armin Schreiner, 29, of the customary
parole review after 15 years in prison for the vileness of his
crime.
</P>
<P>
Schreiner, a trained electrician, admitted on the first day of
the trial that he abducted schoolgirl Natalie Astner of Epfach in
Bavaria in September 1996 for sexual abuse, and then killed her
despite her repeated cries for mercy, throwing her body into a
ditch.
</P>
<P>
Schreiner was released from prison in July 1995 after serving
three years for a child sexual abuse offense.
</P>
<P>
The trial has attracted widespread media attention in Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
