<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France, U.S. Wish to Strengthen Cooperation in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- France and the United States have
expressed wish to install "a spirit of cooperation" rather than
compete with each other over the affairs of Africa, said a French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine and U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright expressed the wish during a meeting in
Brussels on Tuesday, said the spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
"The two ministers wished that the dialogue between Frenchmen
and Americans intensify on the African questions and in a spirit of
cooperation and not in competition," he said.
</P>
<P>
Albright visited last week several African countries including
the Democratic Republic of Congo, Angola, Uganda, Rwanda, Ethiopia,
South Africa and Zimbabwe, which France considers to be within the
American influence zone in Africa.
</P>
<P>
France suffered a series of setbacks in Africa over the past one
year and is now readjusting its Africa policy by extending
cooperations to non-French speaking countries in the black
continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
