<HEADLINE> Coca-Cola to Invest in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Coca-Cola Beverages Ltd. said
it will pour 400 million dollars (280 million U.S. Dollars) into
capital investments in Canada over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The money will be spent on infrastructure -- such as trucks,
vending machines and distributing centers -- to reach customers
and get them to drink more Coke, according to today's Financial
Post newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The company makes about 95 percent of Coke's soft drinks in
Canada, including Sprite, Barq's root beer, Minute Maid fruit
juices and Fruitopia iced teas.
</P>
<P>
The latest move is seen as another step to win back sales lost
to other beverages makers like Cott Corp.
</P>
<P>
Part of Coke's new strategy in Canada will be to focus on
people who don't drink regularly by making it more accessible.
</P>
</TEXT>
