<HEADLINE> Quake Strikes Island off Alaska </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake with a
preliminary magnitude of 6.6 on the Richter scale struck Rat
Island in the Aleutian Island chain off the coast of Alaska
Tuesday night, the United Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
Paul Whitmore of the Pacific Tsunami Warning Center in Palmer,
Alaska said that the quake occurred at 7:39 p.m. local time
Tuesday night (0339 GMT Wednesday). The epicenter of the quake was
about 320 kilometers southwest of Adak Island.
</P>
<P>
Because it happened in a remote area, there were no reports of
damage or injuries.
</P>
<P>
But a warning was issued for Hawaii and other areas of the
Pacific and that some areas of the West Coast may experience small
sea level fluctuations as a result of the quake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
