<HEADLINE> EU, ASEAN to Hold Industrialist Round-Table </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- European industrialists are
to meet Thursday and Friday their equivalents of ASEAN countries
to discuss currency instability as well as investment and
industrial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The round table, the first of its kind between the two unions,
will focus on coping with the current monetary instability in
Thailand and Indonesia, framework conditions for investment and
industrial cooperation, sharing the benefits of technological
progress and challenges arising from the global information
society.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting will take place in Jakarta under the joint
auspices of Hartarto Sastrosoenarto, Indonesian minister for
production and distribution, and Martin Bangemann, European Union
commissioner in charge of industry.
</P>
<P>
The round table is expected to adopt conclusions which may
define the basis for the future of this business dialogue between
the two unions. 
</P>
