<HEADLINE> Germany's Vereinsbank to Take Over Dutch Mortgage Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Bayerische Vereinsbank
Wednesday said it hoped to complete the takeover of the FGH Bank
of Utrecht, one of the top three mortgage banks in the
Netherlands, in the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Munich-based bank said it was acquiring the stake worth 700
million guilders (352 million U.S. dollars) from the Aegon
insurance company of the Hague, which no longer views the FGH Bank
as part of its core operations.
</P>
<P>
The FGH Bank, with assets of about seven billion guilders,
achieved 85 million guilders in profits in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Vereinsbank, which is to merge with its rival Hypo-Bank next
year into Germany's second largest commercial bank, said the
acquisition was in line with the future bank's strategy.  
