<HEADLINE> GCC FMs Complete Preparations for Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from
the six Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) states today completed
final preparations for the three-day summit of their leaders, due
to open here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We have finalized the agenda and the work has been
completed. We are looking forward to seeing a summit that meets
the aspirations of the Gulf citizens," Saudi Foreign Minister
Prince Saud Al-Faisal said here after a meeting of the ministers.
</P>
<P>
