<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Paris public prosecutor
Tuesday opened a judicial inquiry against the leader of
extreme-right National Front, Jean-Marie Le Pen, for his remarks
on gas chamber in Nazi death camps of World War II.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted judicial sources as saying
today that Paris Investigation Judge Jean-Paul Valat is in charge
of the file of Le Pen after the inquiry was opened.
</P>
