that the gas chamber in Nazi death camps was "a detail of the
history of World War II."
</P>
<P>
He could be found guilty of "dispute of crimes against
humanity," an offense which, if convicted, can result in one year
in prison and 300,000 francs (50,000 U.S. dollars) in fines
according to the French law on the press. 
