like to gain humanitarian aid from his country, but (Lebanon
needs) political support of the implementation of the Resolution
425," Hrawi said.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 Israeli troops are occupying a self-styled
security zone of 1,200 square kilometers in south Lebanon with the
declared aim of preventing Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border
attacks on residents in northern Israel. 
