<HEADLINE> Gold Volume Cleared in London Remains High in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The volume of gold
cleared in London last month stood at an average of 40.8
million ounces each day, near the record set in October,
according to figures from the London Bullion Market Association.
</P>
<P>
The amount of gold cleared each day last month in London,
worth 12.5 billion U.S. dollars, was less than the record of
42 million ounces, worth 13.6 billion dollars, established
in October.
</P>
<P>
The association said that in October producers rushed
to hedge their gold output as the price of gold fell sharply.
</P>
<P>
However, November's volume was still 31 percent higher
over the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The association's chief executive Chris Elston said
that although there was perhaps less forward activity last
month in the gold market than in October, physical demand
remained strong and the speculative side was still active.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, last month's silver daily turnover was 327.9
million ounces, worth 1.7 billion dollars, less than the
average of 345.5 million ounces recorded in October, which
was also worth 1.7 billion dollars due to the price rise of
silver in November.  
</P>
</TEXT>
