<HEADLINE> Zambian President Urges to Build More Shopping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba
today called for more new infrastructure, and new housing and
shopping center schemes.
</P>
<P>
He made the appeal when unveiling of corner stone for the Manda
Hill Shopping Center.
</P>
<P>
He said "I am aware that a number of rehabilitation projects are
currently going on as an effort to restore the run-down
infrastructure. commendable as these efforts are, we cannot stop at
mere rehabilitating infrastructure. We need to constantly break new
ground."
</P>
<P>
Chiluba urged professionals in urban development, town planners,
architects, engineers and others to be more forthcoming in
their professions.
</P>
<P>
He also called on district councils to redouble their efforts to
ensure that cities, towns and villages develop in well managed manner.
</P>
<P>
He urged foreign entrepreneurs to come and invest in his country,
saying that "We have provided the necessary enabling environment for
investment in Zambia."
</P>
<P>
Developments such as this shopping centre are common place and they
are essential and convenient to the people because one-stop shopping
centers not only provide a greater choice of goods under one roof but
also cut down on travel time and create savings in fuel, Chiluba said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Those of us who have had the opportunity of visiting other
countries, are aware that most of their town and cities are generally
beautiful and pleasant to live in because of facilities such as
beautiful shopping malls like the one whose construction I am
commissioning today."
</P>
<P>
"This type of development is not beyond us in Zambia. We can, with
proper planning, good workmanship and proper enforcement recapture the
vision of making Lusaka the garden city that it was meant to be," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said some flyover bridges will soon be constructed
around the capital city to make it safe for shoppers and other
pedestrians. 
