<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women Dropouts Plague Ethiopia's College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Female students dominate
those who interrupt their education from Ethiopia's Kotebe
College of Teachers Education due to various reasons, a
psychology instructor in the college said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, At a
symposium organized with a view to look for a solution for the
cultural, psychological and academic problems faced by women,
instructor Semira Al-Hadj said women students are still far
behind in building their self confidence.
</P>
<P>
She said, women seemed to be unable to properly attend their
education due to a feeling of inferiority caused by various
environmental and cultural influences.
</P>
<P>
The participation of women in class activities is very low and
they seem Ato be fearful and shy, Semira said, adding that
consequently they would score very low results.
</P>
<P>
Another instructor, Taitu Ali, said some women students
believe that their comprehension is less than that of men. With
such understanding they turn to men in need of some help, but
would unfortunately be subjected to seduction, she added.
</P>
<P>
She said many such cases have been reported by women students.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the symposium, the head of women affairs
department with the Ministry of Education, Yelfign Worku, said in
order to resolve the problems faced by women students, the
readiness and initiative should first come from the women
themselves.
</P>
<P>
According to the head, women should realize the existence of
the problems and are expected to fight it and come out as
winners. In this respect they would be provided with all the
necessary assistance, she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
