<HEADLINE> Zambia's Inter-Party Dialogue to Be Held as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Zambian's inter-party dialogue will
be held on schedule even if some parties fail to confirm their
attendance by Thursday, the country's ruling party said here today.
</P>
<P>
Micheal Sata, Ntional Secretary of the ruling Movement for the
Multi-Party Democracy (MMD) and government minister without portfolio,
told a news briefing that out of 31 parties which attended the
preliminary meeting early last week and drew an agenda for the
inter-party dialog to be held on January 10 next year, 17 parties
have confirmed their attendance.
</P>
<P>
Sata, who was co-chairman of the preliminary meeting, said most
major political parties have been among the 17 parties including the
United National Independence Party (UNIP) led by former president
Kenneth Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
Sata said it was wrong that some parties were sending complete
lists of delegates to attend the talks because the talks are not
for party cadres but for the leadership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
