<HEADLINE> Kim Dae-jung Ahead in S. Korean Vote Count </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Kim Dae-jung, candidate of the
opposition National Congress for New Politics, is leading the vote
of South Korea's presidential election as of midnight Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Central Election Management Committee, the watchdog of the
presidential election, said that after 55 percent of votes
counted, Kim has temporarily surpassed Lee Hoi-chang, contender of
the Grand National Party, by a 1.8 percentage point, or roughly
260,000 votes.
</P>
<P>
The final outcome of the election will be announced by the
committee in earlier hours of Friday. 
</P>
