<HEADLINE> China, Congo Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He emphasized that peace and stability are important conditions
to national development. What the DRC government is doing is to
realize national stability and make a contribution to regional
peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he appreciates the DRC government's efforts in
restoring political stability and reconstructing their country.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the Congolese visitors on China's proper
treatment of relations among reform, development and stability,
multi-party cooperation and a political consultation system under
the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party, as well as ethnic
unity policy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he hopes the DRC would play an active role in
safeguarding and promoting peace and stability in central Africa.
</P>
<P>
Discussing what is going on in Africa, he said seeking peace,
stability and development is the mainstream of the African
situation.
</P>
<P>
African countries continue active exploration of social systems
and development roads suited to their own national situation,
increase their consciousness of unity and self-reliance, try to
solve African issues by themselves, speed up economic integration
in Africa, and seek higher position and more important roles in
the international arena, he added.
</P>
<P>
Africa is rich in natural resources, and has great development
potential, Jiang said, adding that China believes that as long as
African countries and their peoples make efforts to maintain peace
and stability, further explore suitable economic development
roads, strengthen unity and cooperation with the help of the
international community, then African countries will overcome
obstacles and finally realize peace and stability on the continent.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Kabila invited Jiang to visit the Congo and Jiang thanked
Kabila for the invitation.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two presidents attended a signing ceremony
of four documents including a framework agreement for China to
provide discount loans to DRC, an agreement on bilateral economic
and technology cooperation, a letter exchange on China's small
grants to the DRC, and an agreement on encouraging and protecting
mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Jiang presided over a ceremony to welcome
Kabila and his party.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the welcoming ceremony and talks were
Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun and Qi Jingfa, chairman of the
Chinese Government Reception Committee and vice minister of
Agriculture; Pierre-Victor Mpoyo, DRC minister of Economy,
Industry and Commerce; and Bizima Karaha, DRC minister of Foreign
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Jiang gave a banquet for his visitors tonight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
