<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Foreign Real Estate Project Gets Backing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal
Government is willing to back a Sino-foreign real estate project
in the heart of the city, Mayor Jia Qinglin said in a meeting here
today with Charles Maikish, president of the World Trade Center of
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The trade and commercial complex will be erected in the Qianmen
(Front Gate) area, which is only a stone's throw from Tian'anmen
Square. A general development plan has been approved by city
planning authorities.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment for renovation projects of Beijing's old
downtown area will be welcome. However, designing modern buildings
should be associated with the city's traditional architectural
styles, Jia told Charles Maikish.
</P>
<P>
A Beijing-based transnational corporation, China International
Industries and Commerce, will be the exclusive developer of the
Qianmen project, which will cover a total floor space of 3.5
million square meters.
</P>
<P>
A group of overseas investors and experts of real estate
planning and designing are in Beijing to hold a meeting on the
project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
