<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 14.67 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) lost 14.67 points to 3472.35 Thursday
as against Wednesday's close of 3487.02.
</P>
<P>
The national index dropped by 4.83 points to 1509.86 from
Wednesday's close of 1514.69.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 was quoted down at 337.42 from the previous close
of 338.22 and the U.S. dollar index improved to 143.05 from the
previous close of 142.70.
</P>
<P>
The upward trend was halted and speculatives reacted
marginally, shedding about 15 points in the sensitive index on the
BSE market Thursday due to selling pressure by speculators
triggered by high call money rates of around 40-45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bull operators, who had built up long positions during the
week, preferred to book profits by squaring off their holdings
before the end of account Friday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
