<HEADLINE> Non-Government Bank Opens Branch in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Minsheng Banking
Corporation (CMBC), the first non-government joint stock bank in
the country, today opened a branch in Wuhan City, capital of
central China's Hubei province.
</P>
<P>
It is CMBC's fifth regional branch, following the four others in
Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen cities. The bank was
founded in Beijing in January 12, 1996.
</P>
<P>
