<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Floating Power Station to Be Built in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's
first floating power station was begun today in Wanxian, a city in
southwest China's Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Funded with 30 million U.S. dollars from the United States, the
power station will be built on a barge 65 meters in length by 20
meters in width and five meters high. The barge moves along with
the rise and fall of the water in the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
With the main equipment imported from the Westinghouse Electric
Co., the power station will have 50,000 kilowatts of installed
capacity and is expected to be built in one year.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. investor will have the right to operate the power
station for 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The power station will make full use of the rich natural gas
reserves in Wanxian. 
</P>
</TEXT>
