<HEADLINE> Shenzhen City Government to Do Practical Things for Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The city government of
Shenzhen, a special economic zone in south China's Guangdong
Province, today agreed to invest more than 3.5 billion yuan to do
10 practical things for local residents in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The largest part of investment, 1.61 billion yuan, will be used
to build 9,028 welfare or low-profit apartments for Shenzhen
residents. Other projects include:
</P>
<P>
-- Investing nearly 1.6 billion yuan to upgrade urban traffic
conditions, expand roads, and build fly-overs and pedestrian
overpasses;
</P>
<P>
-- Pouring 160 million yuan into harnessing the Binhe River and
the Luofang wastewater handling system, as well as the renovation
of some drainage pipelines;
</P>
<P>
-- Upgrading the city's commercial areas with an investment of
30 million yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- Purchasing a fleet of buses and adding new bus itineraries,
by investing 28 million yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- Building 50 health-care centers, with an investment of 7.5
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Other efforts include adding telephone booths, establishing
vegetable centers and fueling buses with natural gas.  
</P>
