<HEADLINE> Radio Programs to Mark Macao Countdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- China National Radio (CNR)
held a ceremony today in Beijing to celebrate two upcoming
programs on the two-year countdown of Macao's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The programs, "Basic Law of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR)," and "Historical and Contemporary View of Macao,"
will be broadcast beginning Dec. 20 throughout the two-year
countdown for Macao's return.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Weiyun, a member of the Drafting Committee of the Basic
Law of the Macao SAR, will be the chief editor of the programs on
the Basic Law of the Macao SAR, which will give an overall
introduction on how the law has been drawn up and its main
contents. The other program will be a briefing of Macao's history
and current reality.
</P>
<P>
China Radio International also held a contest on the general
knowledge of Macao, and the overseas edition of "People's Daily"
will open a special column on Macao's changes.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Jianhui, director of the Information Office of the State
Council, said in today's opening ceremony of CNR program, that he
hopes more media will offer programs or launch activities to
acquaint people both in China and overseas with Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
