<HEADLINE> Swedish Economy Picks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Sweden saw a 1.9 percent
growth in its Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in the first three-
quarters of the year, and a 1.6 percent growth in the first half
year.
</P>
<P>
The increases mainly resulted from a growth in private
consumption, which went up by 2.0 percent during the period, and a
positive export trend.
</P>
<P>
The GDP of the third quarter rose by 2.7 percent compared with
the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Also in the third quarter private consumption climbed by 2.0
percent while exports of goods and services soared by 13.7
percent, and imports rose by 11.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
