<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Congo Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called the visit by President Laurent-Desire Kabila of the
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) "very significant" to
sustainable development of bilateral relations during their talks
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Chinese people cherish deep feelings for the
Congolese people, and for a long time the two peoples sympathized
with and supported each other, cooperated sincerely and forged a
firm friendship.
</P>
<P>
Great change has taken place in the Congo's political scene
this year, he said, adding that China appreciates and supports the
DCR government's efforts to explore a development path suited to
its national situation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said: "President Kabila attaches great importance to the
friendship with China. I believe the current visit will help
increase mutual understanding and be very significant to the
sustainable development of bilateral relations."
</P>
<P>
China considers DCR an important partner in Africa, he said,
and added that on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence, China is ready to consolidate and deepen the
friendship between the two peoples, expand mutually beneficial
cooperation in economic and trade areas, promote exchange through
various levels, strengthen consultation and cooperation in
international affairs, and work with the DCR to forge a long-term,
stable and all-round cooperative state-to-state relationship.
</P>
<P>
Appraising bilateral economic and trade cooperation, Jiang said
China encourages its enterprises to invest in the DCR, and will
continue to promote trade between Chinese and DCR companies in
various forms and channels.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said he is very glad to visit China at the invitation of
President Jiang. It is a proof of deep friendship between DCR and
China that his China trip occurs only several months after he took
his post, he noted, and added he hopes the visit would further
strengthen and develop friendly cooperative relations between his
country and China.
</P>
<P>
He said for more than 30 years his country's economic
development has been blocked, and that the DCR government has
mapped out a three-year plan of national reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
China's development has been remarkably fast, he said, adding
that he hopes China will actively participate in the Congo's
reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said he invites Chinese enterprises to invest in the
DCR, and that the Congo is willing to forge a just, cooperative
partnership with China.
</P>
</TEXT>
