<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Resignation of "President" of Somaliland Refused </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Reports from the break away
Republic of Somaliland indicate that the resignation forwarded by
Mohamed Hagi Ibrahim Egal, president of the unrecognized
republic, was not accepted following an emergency session by the
two houses in Hargeisa.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Hargeisa said 129 members from the House of
Elders and the House of Representatives, met and voted for
whether to accept Egal's resignation or refuse. As a result, 124
members voted against Egal's move, while three accepted and two
others, the two chairmen of the houses, abstained.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Egal is left with no choice other than working as the
president of the republic. The two houses said this is the most
crucial moment for Somaliland when a great deal of developments
and peace were achieved during his incumbency in the office,
therefore his resignation is inappropriate and unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
In a letter sent to the two houses on Tuesday, Egal forwarded
his resignation complaining about what he called lack of
collaboration by his people. He said he was disappointed by the
people who just elected him as a president but did not want to
work for the development of their country.
</P>
<P>
The resignation of Egal has been widely talked about in
Somaliland and in Somalia in general. Conservatives in Hargeisa
believe that this is the worst time President Egal could resign
because it would prove the existence of improper administration
and foreigners would start pressuring Somaliland to join the
on-going peace talks in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
However, people opposed to Egal's secessionist policy said
this is the best time he could resign since it is coinciding with
the continuation of the Cairo peace deal between the major
political factions. They believe it is time to integrate with the
rest of Somalia and participate in the continuing power sharing
in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Other non-aligned groups classified Egal's move as merely
power consolidation and that he intends to attract more
supporters in his pretext of showing no ambition for power.
</P>
<P>
People in Mogadishu also received the resignation news with
different reactions. Supporters of Hussein Mohamed Aidid believe
that Egal's move would destabilize the on-going reconciliation
talks in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
"If his resignation is from the heart and he intends to join
the rest of Somalia, it will mean that everything should be
restarted from the beginning," said Abdi Ahmed Dhuhulow, an
influential politician in south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
But the people of north Mogadishu simply welcomed Egal's
resignation. Some political analysts said Egal is merely playing
a game to attract the international attention from Cairo and to
remind the world of his existence and that the cause of
Somaliland is unnegotiable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Improve Management of Skilled Personnel (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He went on to say that three major shifts must happen in
China's personnel work before the management of skilled personnel
could improve substantially.
</P>
<P>
First, he said, personnel departments must expand their service
coverage from the state-owned sector and the cities to the entire
national economy and the countryside.
</P>
<P>
Second, personnel management should no longer be confined to
managing only the so-called "state cadres," or government
employees, but should include the management of all types of
skilled labor.
</P>
<P>
"Finally, and most important of all, every personnel official
must have it in mind that you are no longer merely handling some
simple paperwork on personnel distribution. You're tapping our
country's resource of skilled personnel," Song stressed.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that in the next three years, the Ministry of
Personnel would enhance the training of officials across the
country, annually sending 200 local personnel chiefs abroad to
study.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also cooperate with the U.S. Hughes Company
and the Siemens Corp. of Germany to train 40 personnel managers
from major state-run enterprises each year, he added.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, the Ministry of Personnel worked out a general
plan for the development of China's skilled-personnel resource
through 2010. The ministry also started an ambitious program to
foster a contingent of world-class elites in science and
technology for the next century.
</P>
<P>
To date 29 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities, as
well as 15 cities that enjoy provincial status in the economy,
have come up with their own plans for improving the management of
local skilled personnel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
