<HEADLINE> Securities Industry in East China Province Develops Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The securities trading volume of
East China's Anhui Province hit 66.8 billion yuan in the
January-October period, 18 percent up from last year's total.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Anhui has established 14 companies in trade of
stock exchanges. They have raised a total of 12.2 billion yuan of
capital from both at home and abroad. Of the money, 6.9 billion
yuan came from overseas, accounting for half of overseas
investors' direct investment in Anhui Province in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Interim reports of the province's stock companies showed a 40
percent increase in their major sales and a 60 percent rise
in profits.
</P>
<P>
These companies' net assets take up for 17.7 percent of the
provincial GDP, showing that the securities industry is playing a
more important role in the province's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
