<HEADLINE> Nagano to Ban Portable Phones in Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Spectators will not be allowed
to use portable phones on their seats at the Winter Olympics in
Nagano, Japan, the organizers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Portable phones and pagers are on a list of 19 items banned
from spectator seats at the games starting Feb. 7, said Hirofumi
Isogai, an official of the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The use of such phones in trains, restaurants and some other
public places sometimes leads to complaints in Japan.
</P>
<P>
At Olympic sites, the sounds of ringing and conversation could
disrupt sports like figure skating, which need silence, Isogai
said.
</P>
<P>
If Olympic spectators must use their portable phones, Is seats
and find a place where they won't disturb others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
