<HEADLINE> Thai Army Fires Warning Shots Against Cambodians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Thai troops in Surin province
Wednesday fired warning shots against the warring factions in
Cambodia, cautioning them not to spread fighting onto the Thai
territory.
</P>
<P>
The Thai army's 23rd infantry regiment fired the shots as
mortar and artillery shells from the Cambodian side strayed onto
the Thai border district of Kap Choeng in Surin province.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fighting reportedly resumed on Wednesday for the third
day as Cambodian co-premier Hun Sen's troops launched a fresh
offensive against those forces loyal to deposed co-premier prince
Norodom Ranariddh near the town of O'smach in northwestern
Cambodia, which is opposite to Surin province.
</P>
<P>
Stray shells fell onto rice fields in Thailand two kilometers
from the border, but so far, no farmers were hit, the Thai
military said.
</P>
</TEXT>
