<HEADLINE> Li Peng, Zhu Rongji Meet Financial Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng and
Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, who are both members of the Standing
Committee of the Politburo of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee, met today with participants of national conferences on
finance and taxation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li Peng thanked the country's financial and
taxation workers for their fruitful work which has supported the
ongoing reform, opening-up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
In the period of the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1991-1996), major
reforms taken by the government in the financial and taxation
fields have proven a success, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the financial and taxation workers to understand
the current difficulties and problems existing in the fields,
stressing that in 1998 the country will stick to a moderate
financial and monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to protect legal income and crack down
on illegal earnings, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu reminded the officials that they will face arduous work in
1998. 
</P>
