<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Circular Asks To Curb Extravagance in Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and the State
Council issued a circular today calling on officials and the
people to curb extravagant activities during the coming Chinese
lunar new year period.
</P>
<P>
The next Spring Festival, a traditional Chinese gala, falls on
January 28.
</P>
<P>
The circular asks local governments to ensure the supply of
goods and to organize healthy cultural activities and performances
for local people during the festival days.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are also urged to take good care of poor
families. Funds should be allocated to help poor people spend the
festival merrily, it says.
</P>
<P>
The number of meetings should be cut so as to let leading
officials have enough time to deal with problems in the grass-root
levels, the circular says.
</P>
<P>
It also asks to step up supervision on taxation and financial
activities, and to prevent local departments from making big
expenditures with public funds at the year-end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
