<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Trade Deficit Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The trade deficit of Cyprus
for the first seven months of this year increased by 4.2 percent
compared with that a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The deficit during the period reached 744.3 million Cypriot
pounds (1,488 million U.S. dollars), said a Department of
Statistics and Research report released today.
</P>
<P>
The higher red figure was largely due to a drop of 6.1 percent
in exports which stood at 368.7 million pounds (737.4 million
dollars) during the period.
</P>
<P>
The sharp decrease in exports was attributed to a 45 percent
shrink in agricultural exports, which recorded only 25.6 million
pounds (51.2 million dollars) in the first seven months of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
