<HEADLINE> China's Largest Publications Wholesale Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The first-phase project of
China's largest publications wholesale market, the Hubei
Provincial Publications and Culture Center, entered operations
today.
</P>
<P>
The market represents yet another important step the Chinese
Government has introduced in recent years to rectify the
marketing of illegal publications.
</P>
<P>
The deputy director of the Hubei Provincial Press and
Publications Bureau said the market is mainly engaged in
wholesaling publications, publishing information, high-tech
development, personnel training, and cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The center, which covers 320,000 sq.m. and was built at a cost
of 1.2 billion yuan, will be totally completed by the end of this
century.
</P>
<P>
The State Press and Publications Administration has selected
six cities, including Beijing and Wuhan, to establish state level
publishing centers, and plans to establish four audio-visual
wholesale centers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Wuhan.
</P>
</TEXT>
