<HEADLINE> Kipketer Voted the Athlete of the Year in Reuters Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Wilson Kipketer, who smashed
the men's 800 meters world record twice this year, has been named
as the 1997 Sports Personality in a Reuters poll here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer scored an impressive 220 points from a maximum 505.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 sports journalists from 43 countries ranked their
leading five sportsmen and women from a 30-strong list compiled by
Reuters sports correspondents, with five points went to the first
place, four points to the second and so on.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer, the Kenyan-born Dane, who beat Sebstian Coe's
16-year-old 800 meters outdoor world record twice and indoor
global mark as many times this season, beat U.S. golfer Tiger
Woods and Swiss tennis player Martina Hingis. Tiger collected 166
points while Hingis accumulated 163.
</P>
<P>
Kipketer chalked up a sensational time of one minute 41.11
seconds on August 13 at the Cologne Grand Prix meet to cut 0.62
seconds off the Coe's 1981 record.
</P>
<P>
He also won the IAAF Grand Prix finals and was named IAAF's
Male Athlete of the Year last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
