<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Section of Hangzhou Expressway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Shanghai
section of the Shanghai-Hangzhou Expressway was completed today.
</P>
<P>
The 151-kilometer expressway links Shanghai, China's largest
industrial center, and Hangzhou, a nationwide scenic spot in
Zhejiang Province. It is a key project listed by the Central
Government for the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai section starts from Xinzhuang in the southwestern
part of the city and ends at Jinshan District on the border
between Shanghai and Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
The 48-kilometer section has 18 bridges. Its construction cost
2.14 billion yuan, including 60 million US dollars provided by the
World Bank in loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
