<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmers Enthusiastic in Construction of Water Conservancy Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in east China's Anhui
province have contributed more than half of the funds for water
conservancy projects in the province this year.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials say this is the unprecedented enthusiasm
shown by the farmers in Anhui for such projects in a decade.
</P>
<P>
By December 5, Anhui has invested 622 million yuan on the
construction of water conservancy projects, 371 million of the
fund coming from farmers. Over 62,000 projects have so far been
completed.
</P>
<P>
An official in the Provincial Water Resources Council said
that construction of water conservancy projects in Anhui has
reached its high tide and it will last until next spring.
</P>
<P>
Anhui is prone to floods and launches a battle against floods
every winter.  
</P>
</TEXT>
