<HEADLINE> China to Improve Management of Skilled Personnel (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
here today that personnel departments across the country next year
should focus on improving their management of skilled personnel to
assist economic development.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a three-day conference of provincial officials in
charge of personnel, Song Defu, minister of personnel, said the
issue of skilled personnel is of strategic importance to China's
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He said that personnel officials should help skilled personnel,
who are urgently needed in the national economy or engaged in
advanced study, obtain preferential treatment in daily life and
scientific research.
</P>
<P>
"We should also encourage higher-education institutions and
enterprises to jointly recruit post-doctorate students to ensure
these young elites work for the enterprises after graduation," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the state has decided to guarantee the
research funds of a number of scholars studying overseas who have
returned home with impressive academic records.
</P>
<P>
He analyzed that China's current policy of developing multiple
ownership, restructuring industries and reforming the state
enterprises would surely add momentum to the flow of skilled
personnel and lead to a new high in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
"We must seize this opportunity and step up building the
special labor markets for skilled personnel, to guarantee an
orderly flow and a reasonable distribution of skilled personnel
across the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged personnel departments at all levels to improve
their services and set up a complete and up-to-date system for
personnel proxy, skilled-personnel appraisal and arbitration of
personnel disputes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
