<HEADLINE> Seizinger Equalls Killy Record in World Cup Super-G </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Katja Seizinger equalled French
legend Jean-Claude Killy's 1967 record of winning six consecutive
World Cup speed events when she triumphed in the women's super-G
in Val D'isere, France, Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The German Olympic champion won in one minute 7.09 seconds to
beat Austrian Renate Goetschl by two hundredths of a second.
</P>
<P>
Fellow German Hilde Gerg was 55 hundredths of a second behind
in third place.
</P>
<P>
Seizinger has won three downhills and three super-G races this
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
