<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Makes Achievements in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam made great achievements
in foreign trade in 1997 despite regional monetary and financial
crises.
</P>
<P>
Reports from relevant agencies said Vietnam's export turnover
reached 8.7 billion U.S. dollars in 1997, a 20 percent increase
over the year.
</P>
<P>
The country's total imports stood at 11.2 billion dollars in
1997, up 0.5 percent compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
Earnings from raw material and semi-processed products
accounted for over 70 percent of the country's total export
turnover.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's main exports including crude oil, rice, coffee,
rubber, tea, aquatic products, and footwear continued to rise.
</P>
<P>
However, due to a lack of investment in new technology,
Vietnamese industries could not turn out many high quality
internationally competitive products.
</P>
<P>
Only the garments, textiles and leather and shoe industries
are maintaining high technological renovation, with an export
turnover of between 960 million and 1.2 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
