<HEADLINE> China Builds Nuclear Power Station at Lianyungang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIANYUNGANG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- China has started building
a nuclear power station in a village in the port city of
Lianyungang in East China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The facility is a Sino-Russian cooperation project signed
by the two countries' premiers last year.
</P>
<P>
