<HEADLINE> HK To Launch Exposition on Information Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's first-ever
public exposition on information infrastructure is to be held
early next year, it was known here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled for February 12-15,1998, the Hong Kong Information
Infrastructure Exposition will promote public understanding of the
importance of building Hong Kong's information infrastructure and
its impact on daily life.
</P>
<P>
It echoes the policy address delivered by Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
which stresses the information infrastructure to boost
Hong Kong's development into the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) and
Office of the Telecommunications Authority, the exposition will
compose of three parts, a commercial exhibition, a Future Society
pavilion and a two-day conference.
</P>
<P>
A special pavilion called "TechWorld '98" co-organized by the
Hong Kong Industrial Technology Center Corporation will
accommodate information technology start-up companies and small
and medium enterprises.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 visitors and 600 conference attendees are
expected to the four-day exposition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
