<HEADLINE> SKorea's Opposition Candidate Leads in Presidential Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Kim Dae-jung, candidate of the
opposition National Congress for New Politics, is leading in
South Korea's presidential election, according to a poll by the
Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The poll carried out among 2,500 voters across the nation shows
that Kim has won 39.9 percent of the votes, one percentage point
ahead of Lee Hoi-chang, candidate of the Grand National Party.
</P>
<P>
The final outcome of the election would be published officially
no later than Friday's dawn, according to the Central Election
Management Commission. 
</P>
