<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stock Prices Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange plunged 379.42 points, or 2.29 percent
from Wednesday's close to 16,161.64.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, fell 15.02 points, or 1.22 percent to
1,212.93.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section came to an estimated 450 million
shares, down from Wednesday's 615.06 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Food stuff trader Toshoku was today' most actively traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Market participants stepped up profit-taking selling, despite
an absence of major market-moving factors, after a surprising two
trillion yen tax cut plan was unveiled Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,329 issues listed on the First Section, losers led
gainers 850 to 303 with 138 issues unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar drifted at the
lower 127 yen level, erasing losses stemming from selling interest
amid talks that the Bank of Japan (BOJ) had again intervened in
the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
