<HEADLINE> 19 Tonnes of Drugs Seized in Central Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Iranian anti-drug forces seized
19 tonnes of various kinds of illicit drugs in Iran's central
province of Kerman so far in the current Iranian year starting
March 21.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA quoted commander of the
provincial security forces Colonel Abass Ali Rouhi as saying today
that the haul was 3,700 kilograms more than the amount seized
during the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
He said that 3,870 smugglers were arrested, 37 smuggling gangs
broken up, and 310 vehicles confiscated during the operations.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three days 1.5 tonnes of narcotics was seized and
several bands of smugglers busted, he added.
</P>
<P>
Iran is a main transit point of drug traffic from the "Golden
Crescent" in the border area of Afghanistan, Pakistan and Iran to
Europe. The country confiscated an average of 150 tonnes of
various narcotics since its adoption of the anti-drug law in
1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
