<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Loans to Bangladesh, Viet Nam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) on Thursday approved a 40 million U.S. dollar loan and an
equity investment of 10 million dollars to establish a cement
plant in Bangladesh with an annual production capacity of 1.2
million tons.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank said in a news release that the loan has
an amortization period of 12 years. A floating interest rate is to
be determined in accordance with the bank's market-based loan
facility.
</P>
<P>
The project, one of the biggest private sector projects in the
country, will promote infrastructure development and construction
activities that will benefit the entire population.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the bank also approved a technical assistance
loan of 2.6 million U.S. dollars for the study of a multi-purpose
water resources project in southern Viet Nam.
</P>
<P>
The study will involve the design of a 25 meter river barrage,
three subsidiary reservoirs, an 8.5 kilometer diversion channel, a
40 kilometer canal and irrigation system and a five megawatt
hydroelectric plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
