<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Tackles Housing Shortages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Zhou, a worker in
Cangzhou City of north China's Hebei Proince, has been extremely
happy these days, for he can celebrate the coming new year in his
new apartment with central heating.
</P>
<P>
His five-member family, who had been huddling in a
30-square-meter room for years, was one of the 72,000 households
with housing problems in Hebei which have moved into spacious
houses in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
According to Liu Cai, Director of the Provincial Housing Reform
Office, the province has since 1995 built houses for low- and
middle-income people with a total floor space of 2.41 million
square meters.
</P>
<P>
In addition, over four million square meters of more economical
houses were completed last year.  
