<HEADLINE> HK Legislature Election Guidelines Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The proposed election
guidelines for the Hong Kong Legislative Council election was
published on Thursday for public consultation.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong people can express their views up to the end of
this month on the draft guidelines on election-related activities
for the Legislative Council general election next May and the
Election Committee subsector election next April.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Justice Woo Kwok-hing, chairman of the
Electoral Affairs Commission, at a press conference here this
morning.
</P>
<P>
He said the draft guidelines have been drawn up by the
Electoral Affairs Commission to ensure the elections be conducted
honestly, fairly and openly.
</P>
<P>
The proposed guidelines, in 17 chapters, deal with a range of
issues that candidates and their agents have to take heed of in
running their campaigns, detailed arrangements on the polling day
and complaint procedures, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We shall carefully consider all representations to be made
during the two-week public consultation exercise before making
regulations governing electoral procedures and finalizing the
guidelines," Woo added.
</P>
<P>
The revised guidelines are expected to be published in
February next year.
</P>
<P>
The 60-member Legislative Council will be made up of 20 seats
to be returned from five geographical constituencies, 30 seats
from 28 functional constituencies and 10 seats from the 800-member
Election Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
