<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Groups of While Fin Dolphins Found in Jiangxi Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have found
that the river section of the Yangtze and the Boyang Lake in
Jiangxi Province, East China, are the home of white fin dolphins
(Chinese river dolphins).
</P>
<P>
In a recent survey, large numbers of white fin dolphins were
located in the 151.9-kilometer river section and the Boyang Lake.
</P>
<P>
The survey, organized by the Ministry of Agriculture, was
conducted in early November in the lower and middle mainstream of
the Yangtze as well as in the waters of the Boyang and
Dongting lakes, the first and second largest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The dolphins were first found in the river section in Jiujiang
County on November 5, and large groups of dolphins were found in
the waters at Balijiang and Laoyemiao of the Boyang Lake in the
following days.
</P>
<P>
Based on the survey, the experts believed that the
Jiujiang section of the Yangtze River and the Boyang Lake are
ideal natural preserves for dolphins, for the waters are less
polluted and rich in feed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
