<HEADLINE> Philippines, Laos Sign Economic Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines and the Lao
People's Democratic Republic on Thursday signed two agreements to
bolster bilateral relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two accords are the agreement on economic and technical
cooperation, and the agreement on agriculture and forestry
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by the two countries' agriculture
ministers in the presence of Philippine President Fidel Ramos and
Lao Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone at the Philippine
Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement on agricultural and forestry cooperation,
the two countries vowed to work closely in all fields of
agriculture and forestry.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be effected through research and training
opportunities, promotion of joint ventures in the production,
processing and marketing of agricultural commodities, and the
exchange of expertise, improved technologies, and information.
</P>
<P>
For the effective implementation of the agreements, a joint
committee will be created and will consist of an equal number of
representatives from both countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the economic and technical cooperation accord, the two
countries agreed to promote the preparation and implementation of
economic and technical projects of mutual interest and the
Philippines will offer to Laos mutually-beneficial expertise and
training programs.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also calls for the establishment of a joint
committee which will examine its implementation, and discuss
issues that might arise concerning the accord.
</P>
<P>
The two agreements were signed following the meeting between
President Ramos and Lao Prime Minister Khamtay who arrived here on
Wednesday for a three-day visit to the Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
