<HEADLINE> Seven People Killed in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed in
road accidents across Indian capital New Delhi on Thursday, Press
Trust of India (PTI) quoted police as saying here.
</P>
<P>
Two motorcyclists were run over by a vehicle at Alipur area
while a pedestrian and an unidentified person were hit at the
city's Narela and Jehanjirpuri respectively.
</P>
<P>
A 15-year-old cyclist died on the spot when a speeding truck
hit him from the back.
</P>
<P>
While an unidentified youth was found dead on Timarpur road in
north Delhi, the body of another unidentified man was found at
Hauz Khas in south Delhi, police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
