<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Krupp Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here this afternoon with Gerhard Cromme, chairman of the board
of directors of the Krupp Company.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Cromme attended the signing ceremony for the
Shanghai-Krupp Stainless Steel Corp., a joint venture between
Krupp-Thyssen Stainless Co. Ltd. and Shanghai Pudong Iron and
Steel Group.
</P>
<P>
Jiang congratulated Cromme and spoke highly of the new
project. He said that China and Krupp have a long history of
co-operation, and noted the two side established trade relations
over a century ago.
</P>
<P>
The president expressed the hope that Krupp will continue
to invest in China and expand its spheres of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, a stainless sheet steel producer involving
total investments of over 1.4 billion US dollars, is the largest
German-investment project in China and also the largest joint
venture in China's metallurgical industry.
</P>
<P>
Cromme said the project, Krupp's largest overseas project since
its founding, marks another major event in its business in China.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed that Krupp will provide advanced technology to
China in a bid to develop the plant into one of the best stainless
steel manufacturers in the country and in the world as well.
</P>
<P>
Krupp, established in 1811, is Germany's major nonferrous
metals supplier, as well as one of the world's leading suppliers
of flat steel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
