<HEADLINE> New Oilfield in NW China Performs Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shixi Oilfield in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region is expected to produce
870,000 tons of oil this year.
</P>
<P>
The oilfield, located in the Junggar Basin, has verified
reserves of 120 million tons of oil and 29.8 billion cubic meters
of gas.
</P>
<P>
By the end of November, 155 oil wells in the oilfield had been
put into production, each producing at least 3,000 tons a
day. Shixi entered trial operations in March, 1995.
</P>
<P>
An oil pipeline currently links Shixi with Karamay City and a
147-km highway has opened to traffic. Work on other
infrastructure projects such as waterworks, power plants and
telecommunications networks are nearing completion.
</P>
<P>
Oil output in the Junggar Basin is expected to reach
8.7 million tons this year, 400,000 tons more than last
year's.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
