<HEADLINE> German Electronic Manufacturer Starts Operation in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Production base of
Hottering Bolduin Electronic Measuring Group (HBM) is now
operational in Suzhou, in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
A senior manager with HBM said recently at the opening ceremony
of the HBM (Suzhou) Co., Ltd. that Suzhou was chosen as HBM's
production base in Asia because the city offers best opportunities
and conditions.
</P>
<P>
HBM, a strain foil and sensing unit manufacturer, occupies 60
percent of the international market share. The construction of the
HBM (Suzhou) Co. started in last April. The strain foils produced
by the company have all passed the quality test after exported
back to Germany.  
</P>
