<HEADLINE> China's Most Impoverished Area Eliminating Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Xihaigu area of China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, which is known as China's most
impoverished area, plans to completely eliminate poverty by the
end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Ma Qizhi, the region's acting chairman, made the statement in a
recent interview with Xinhua. He said, "The area's remaining
760,000 people will live a better life at the end of the century,
with 600 yuan in per-capita annual income and 300 kg of grain."
</P>
<P>
Xihaigu is in a mountainous area in southern Ningxia. It has
2.2 million people and is burdened with difficult geographical
conditions.
</P>
<P>
China has 58 million poor people, about a 20th of the world's
total. The central government promised in 1993 that it would help
them get out of poverty by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
So, the central government is allotting 30 million yuan for
Xihaigu annually, to improve infrastructure, because the
elimination of poverty there will be significant to the rest of
the nation in the anti-poverty campaign.
</P>
<P>
A railway has been opened in the area, there are roads to every
township, and all villages have electricity.
</P>
<P>
A new irrigation method -- rainwater irrigation -- will be used
there, the chairman said, adding that the region will participate
in a water diversion project, from the Yellow River, that will
irrigate 140,000 ha of land, as part of a resettlement program for
740,000 poor people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
