<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Loans Upgrade Infrastructure in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Intensified inflow of overseas
funds, overseas government loans in particular, has helped north
China's Tianjin Municipality improve the investment climate in its
coastal New Area, the city's economic powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
Preferred for its long duration and low interest rate, the
overseas government loans helped upgrade the infrastructural
facilities in the New Area, which comprises the Tianjin Economic
and Technology Development Zone, the Tianjin Port Bonded Zone, and
some other areas along the coast.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Economic and Technology Development Zone, for
instance, has introduced 14.5 million US dollars in foreign
government lendings for projects in heat supply, sewage treatment,
waste water processing, garbage incineration, and environment
protection.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the Tianjin Port Bonded Zone said his
zone welcomes foreign government loans to further promote its
investment environment. The zone has a total of more than 3,000
tax-free ventures and foreign trade companies.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Tianjin used a total of 1.2 billion US
dollars in overseas funds between 1982 and 1996 and reported good
repayment records. 
</P>
</TEXT>
