<HEADLINE> China to Carry out Obligations on Banning Chemical Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- China will seriously carry out
its due obligations as a signatory state of the Convention on the
Banning of Chemical Weapons to assure the realization of the
purpose and goal of the convention.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang made this
statement at a weekly press conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
China opposes the development of chemical weapons by any
country, nor will it help any country to develop such weapons,
Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted that as a victim of chemical weapons in the second
World War, China "has a bigger say than any other country on this
matter."  
