<HEADLINE> Good Year For China's Diplomacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- China has "achieved successes
in diplomacy this year", China's Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen said in a recent interview with People's Daily, and
called it "an extraordinary year" for China.
</P>
<P>
China's Good-neighborly relations of friendship with
surrounding countries have increased and unity with developing
nations strengthened, and at the same time, relations with the
Western countries have improved, he said.
</P>
<P>
Especially, he pointed out, there has been overall improvement
and increase in China's relations with the major powers.
</P>
<P>
China has called for a new type of state-to-state non-aligned,
non-confrontational relations that are not directed at a third
party, Qian said, adding that China is advocating a new security
concept of increased trust through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
China has been active in international and regional diplomatic
activities and economic co-operation, Qian said, and in this way,
has played a unique and active role in promoting world peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
He attributes these successes to Deng Xiaoping's ideas on
diplomacy and China's independent foreign policy of peace. In the
future world structure, he said, China will be an active force for
maintaining peace and stability of the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the UN Security Council, he said,
China fully recognizes its responsibilities and obligations and is
playing a constructive role and striving to establish fair and
reasonable international political and economic orders.
</P>
<P>
It is ridiculous to regard China's economic development as a
"threat", he commented, pointing out that, in the past China was
bullied by the big powers and well remembers the ancient proverb
of not imposing on others what you yourself do not desire. China
will never be hegemonic when it is developed in the future, he
concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
