<HEADLINE> Search for Missing Ukrainian Plane Resumed in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Rescue teams supported by Greek
air force planes, army units and local farmers resumed their
search Thursday for a Ukrainian plane carrying 73 people that
disappeared shortly before landing at the Macedonia airport in
northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Russian-built Yakovlev 42, on route from Kiev to
Thessaloniki, vanished from radar screens at 21:15 local time
while at an altitude of 3200 feet as it flew over the Greek town
of Veria, the Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Two Hercules C-130 planes and two Shinuk helicopters flew over
the region of Pieria mountains, Imathia and Kozani covered by
1.5-meter-deep snow while police assisted by local farmers in
tractors and command units combed the area.
</P>
<P>
Coast guard patrol boats, fishing boats and tugboats also
searched the sea region around Thessaloniki and Katerini.
</P>
<P>
Among the 62 passengers, 20 are foreigners and 42 Greeks. Most
of the Greeks are businessmen or workers coming home for Christmas
and new year holidays.
</P>
<P>
An initial report said that the plane had crashed soutwest of
Thessaloniki, but this has not been confirmed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
