<HEADLINE> EU Motion on Removing China from List of Non-Market Economy Countries Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Removing China from the
European Union's (EU) list of non-market economy countries will
promote the further development of Sino-European economic and
trade cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang made the
remarks during today's regular press conference.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question concerning the Tuesday's EU motion to
remove China from its list of non-market economy countries, Tang
said China has noticed discussions of the motion in the EU
anti-dumping policy. "China welcomes and appreciates the motion
which is both positive and wise," said Tang.
</P>
<P>
China does not oppose anti-dumping in the general sense, but
does oppose discriminatory anti-dumping. said Tang, adding that
China sincerely hopes the EU will objectively consider the actual
situation concerning China's economy and make the correct
judgement.  
