<HEADLINE> S. African Police Probe Multi-Million Rand Heist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The South African police
this morning were combing the scene of a 10 million Rand (roughly
2 million U.S. Dollars) cash-in-transit robbery in Mpumalanga
Province in which six security guards were killed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The South African Press Association reported today that a gang
of 20 robbers attacked two armored vehicles belonging to SBV
Security, a company which transports cash for the country's major
banks.
</P>
<P>
The robbers used a stolen truck to force the armored vehicles
off the road between Kwaggasfontein and Siyabuswa, some 80
kilometers northeast of Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
The truck crashed into the two security vehicles, causing one
of them to overturn. Three guards were killed in the crash.
</P>
<P>
The other three security guards were shot dead by the robbers.
</P>
<P>
One survived long enough to give police some information about
the attack. He later died at the scene.
</P>
<P>
Bank robberies and robberies of cash in transit are
commonplace in South Africa, which is among countries with the
highest crime rates in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
