<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Gets 1.3 Billion Dollars Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has received investment
pledges totalling 1.3 billion U.S. Dollars since 1993, according
to the Standard Chartered Bank.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of the sum went into manufacturing which accounted
for 35 percent of the total pledges while agriculture accounted
for 26 percent.
</P>
<P>
The transport sector received 14 percent, tourism 6 percent
and the remaining went to other sectors.
</P>
<P>
But statistics from Zambia Investment Center show a steep fall
in investment flows this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months the center issued licenses worth 156
million Dollars, which is the lowest in recently years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the 1997 World Investment Report indicates that
Zambia's foreign owned capital stock has grown to one billion
Dollars by 1996 from 684 million in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
