<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Says China-ASEAN Relations Entering New Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen has said the Joint Statement of the
Summit of the People's Republic of China and the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) marks a new stage in China-ASEAN
relations.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks in a recent interview with People's
Daily,
</P>
<P>
Qian said ASEAN has become a major force in the Asian-Pacific
region and the world as well and China will continue to support
the positive role of ASEAN in the region.
</P>
<P>
China has made progress in relations with ASEAN, he said, and
the two have established a partnership of comprehensive dialog
and full cooperation.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin attended the informal summit of ASEAN,
China, Japan and the Republic of Korea, and the leaders discussed
increasing cooperation in various fields. They also issued a joint
statement on establishing a good-neighbor partnership of mutual
trust for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
As a developing country, China has always treasured its
relations with other developing countries, Qian said, adding that
the friendly cooperative relations between China and other
developing countries have been strengthened since the beginning of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have conducted exchanges and cooperation in
various fields in line with the principles of equality, mutual
benefit, complementary advantages and common development, Qian
said, and progress has been made in the fields of economy and
trade.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
