<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Stand-By Credit for Estonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) today approved a 15-month stand-by credit of about 22
million U.S. dollars for Estonia to support its 1998 economic
program.
</P>
<P>
However, the Estonian authorities have indicated they might not
draw on the money, as was the case of the stand-by credit that
expired in August 1997.
</P>
<P>
Estonia's 1998 economic program aims to achieve an annual
growth rate of real GDP of over 5 percent, with inflation rate
further dropping to about 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Estonia joined the IMF in May 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
