<HEADLINE> Albania's Lawmaker Sentenced to 11-Year Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Gafur Mazreku, an Albanian
lawmaker from the Socialist Party, was sentenced to an 11-year
imprisonment by a local court in Tirana Wednesday for alleged
shooting of another legislator, Azem Hajdar.
</P>
<P>
The conviction was announced after 12 trials against Mazreku,
who shot Hajdar and seriously wounded him in parliament on
September 18, after the two came to blows during a legislative
session.
</P>
<P>
Hajdar, a Democratic Party member, was hit five times in his
chest and right leg.
</P>
<P>
"I did not want to kill him. Only wound him," Mazreku told a
court hearing.
</P>
<P>
The incident caused a serious political turmoil in Albania. The
Democrats have been staging daily rallies in central Albania to
condemn the shooting, and demanded the resignation of the
Socialist-led government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
