<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Opens Wider To Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
built two state-level hi-tech development zones in Hefei, the
provincial capital, and in Wuhu respectively, as well as 19
province-level development zones.
</P>
<P>
Province-level foreign trade companies now contribute 55
percent of the province's foreign trade, down from the nearly 92
percent in 1992, but the foreign trade volume of prefecture-level
companies is now at least 12 times the figure of five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The province has gotten 640 million US dollars in overseas
investment this year, including 180 million US dollars in loans.
</P>
<P>
The number of local overseas-funded enterprises has risen from
880 in 1992 to the current 2,000, which are spread across the
province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
