<HEADLINE> Senior CPC leader Meets VCP Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Jia Qinglin, member of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee met here today with a delegation from the Viet Nam
Communist Party (VCP), led by Nong Hong Thai, member of VCP
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jia, also secretary of Beijing Municipal Committee of the CPC,
spoke highly of the comprehensive development of friendly cooperative
ties between the two countries and the two parties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the friendship between Chinese and
Vietnamese people will bring long-term, stable and
good-neighborly friendly relations into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Nong Hong Thai, also secretary of Cao Bang Provincial Committee
of the VCP, noted that China has scored marked achievement in its
reform and opening up, and noted that Viet Nam wants to learn
more from China's experience.
</P>
<P>
Li Chengren, deputy director of the International Department of
the CPC Central Committee, Vu Quang Khoat, Vietnamese charge
d'affaires ad interim also attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Nong Hong Thai and his party arrived here on Tuesday as guests
of International Department of the CPC Central Committee. Li
Chengren met with the delegation on Wednesday.  
</P>
