<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-Governmental Diplomacy Promotes Sino-Foreign Economic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 Chinese cities
have established friendly relations with some 500 foreign cities
in 80 countries and have brought in more than 10 billion US
dollars in foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
At a national conference held recently, an official of the
Beijing-based Chinese People's Association for Friendship with
Foreign Countries, said that since the port city of Tianjin
established friendly relations with Japan's Kobe City in 1973, the
number of Sino-foreign friendly cities has increased at an average
annual rate of 50.
</P>
<P>
He said that 80 percent of those cities are located along
China's coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
He said with the help of the friendly relations, more than 600
trade fairs have been held in those cities in the past few years
and deals worth over 6 billion dollars have been made.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 1,200 projects have been
launched in these Chinese cities with investment from their
foreign sister cities.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, the national and local associations for
friendship with foreign countries have sponsored dozens of
international economic symposiums which provided cooperation
opportunities for Chinese and foreign cities.
</P>
<P>
Experts believed that the establishment of Sino-foreign
friendly cities has become a major channel for Sino-foreign
economic and trade cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
