<HEADLINE> Over 100 Die of Cholera in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 18 (Xinhua) -- With nine more reported
dead in the last 24 hours, death toll of cholera victims in
Zanzibar has surpassed 100, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The Daily News said that six cholera patients died at hospital
yesterday, while three more bodies were brought to hospital from
outside for burial arrangements in accordance with cholera
regulations.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the situation is still serious with children and
women being the most affected.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) has deployed two
medical donors, two vehicles, a large shipment of supplies,
including much needed ringers lactate, oral rehydration salts and
doxycline, hospital beds and lysol for cleansing.
</P>
<P>
The Zanzibar government has obtained 100 tons of medical
supplies from businessmen and international organizations.
</P>
<P>
A study, done by the Ministry for Health, has revealed that
the source of the epidemic was the lack of latrines and waste
disposal pits.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, cholera had killed a total of 1,780 people by
December 6, the Principal Secretary in the Health Ministry, Ray
Mrope, told the Guardian on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
