<BODY>
<HEADLINE> About 100,000 Nepalese Women Work in Indian Brothels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 18 (Xinhua) -- About 70,000 to 100,000
Nepalese women and children are working in Indian brothels, The
Kathmandu Post newspaper Thursday quoted a survey as saying.
</P>
<P>
About 30 percent of them are under the age of 18 and 70 percent
illiterate, said the survey sponsored by the Central Social
Welfare Board.
</P>
<P>
The major factors contributing to the commercial sexual
exploitation of women and children are poverty and unemployment or
lack of appropriate rehabilitation, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Forty-five percent of them want to be rescued from the
brothels, the survey added.
</P>
<P>
Trafficking in women and girls across the 1,750-kilometre-long
open Indo-Nepal border is one of the most pressing issues in
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that around 5,000 to 7,000 Nepalese women and
girls are trafficked every year for flesh trade in India and other
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
