<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Beats United States 5-4 in Women's Ice Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Jayna Hefford scored two
goals, including the decisive one with 2:05 remaining, to lead the
Canadian women's Olympic ice hockey team to a 5-4 victory over the
United States in Burlington, Vermont on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The United States led 4-1 early in the second period, but wilted
in the face of aggressive Canadian play.
</P>
<P>
In the final period, U.S. goaltender Erin Whitten did
everything she could to protect a one-goal lead. But Whitten
couldn't overcome aggressive Canadian forechecking and sloppy
defensive play in front of her.
</P>
<P>
Hefford scored the winning goal on a shot from in close.
</P>
<P>
The game is part of the Three Nations' Cup pre-Olympic series.
</P>
<P>
Both teams are preparing for the Winter Olympics in Nagano,
Japan, in February. Canada now leads the pre-Olympic series
between the teams 5-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
