<HEADLINE> India Identifies New Areas to Boost Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
identified six more areas that will help it formulate an action
plan for the next 10 years in the tourism sector, official sources
said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new areas are: infrastructure, taxation, facilitation at
airports, human resource development, effective marketing and
incorporating information technology in the accounting system.
</P>
<P>
The new tourism policy is yet to be approved by the cabinet.
The Tourism Ministry will start work in areas that will lay the
foundation for development of tourism in India once the new policy
is approved.
</P>
<P>
A supervisory agency in international airports is imperative to
woo tourists. The new body will co-ordinate the agencies involved
in clearing passengers, especially foreign tourists, at
international airports.
</P>
<P>
Attracting tourists is as important as creating an impression
which will make them return to India, starting from the airport
itself, with facilities like good, clean taxis and quick clearance
at the immigration counters, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Tourism Ministry said that India must start
offering adventure tourism to promote tourism as a whole in the
country.  
</P>
