<HEADLINE> IDB Launches New $85 million Medium-Term Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the launching of a new 150
billion Italian lira (about 85 million U.S. dollars) bond issue
under its Euro Medium-Term Note Program.
</P>
<P>
The previous issue in lira for a similar amount was launched by
the IDB on December 1.
</P>
<P>
The issue is priced at 100.908 percent and pays an annual
coupon of 12.15 percent for the first year and 7 percent for the
second and third years. In the fourth year and in subsequent
years, the issue pays a coupon of 15.5 percent minus two times the
12-month Italian lira Libor times 365/360, with a minimum coupon
of zero percent.
</P>
<P>
The bond issue was launched on December 17, and will mature on
January 15, 2010.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue were swapped into U.S. dollars and
will be incorporated into the IDB's ordinary capital and used to
help finance the economic and social development projects in Latin
America and the Caribbean. 
</P>
</TEXT>
