<P>
COLOMBO, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will participate in
the Expo'98 to be held in Lisbon, Portugal, from May to September
next year, a government official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Amarasinghe, president of the Federation of Chambers of
Commerce and Industry, said his federation has been authorized by
the Cabinet to organize Sri Lanka's pavilion at the expo.
</P>
<P>
About 135 countries will be presented on the major world trade
fair, which could attract some 23 million visitors, Amarasinghe
said.
</P>
<P>
He said it would be a real opportunity for Sri Lanka to project
its national image on the fair.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's cultural heritage, tourism industry, trade and
indigenous products, such as handicrafts, jewelry and tea, will be
promoted during the four-month event, Amarasinghe said.  
</P>
