<HEADLINE> Auto Sales Remain Dim in November in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Auto sales totaled 12,783
units in Thailand last month, down 73.4 percent year-on-year,
according to the latest statistics by Toyota motor Thailand
available here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The auto sales last month almost remained unchanged from 12,776
units in October, the auto marketing leader in Thailand said.
</P>
<P>
Monthly auto sales have shrunk significantly this year, from
30,866 units in August to 14,136 in September, the company said.
</P>
<P>
The total sales in the first 11 months this year reached
347,986 units, down 34.5 percent compared with the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The 11 month sales of pickup trucks totaled 221,529 units, down
40.7 percent, while passenger car sales slipped 19.6 percent to
126,457 units.
</P>
<P>
Total sales by Japanese auto makers fell 34.8 percent to
316,904 units, taking the market share of 91 percent during the 11
months this year.
</P>
<P>
The company also predicts that auto sales in Thailand will
slide down to 180,000 to 240,000 units next year as the Thai
economy is expected to enter deeper into recession.  
</P>
</TEXT>
