<HEADLINE> Argentina, Chile To Sign Agreement On Mining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Argentina and Chile will
sign an agreement on cooperative mining this year, Argentina`s
Secretary of Industry, Commerce and Mining, Alieto Guadagni,
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will allow investors in both countries to explore
new mineral fields and exploit mines in the mountain range that
forms the common frontier.
</P>
<P>
The document will also include a frame of reference and tax
scale in accordance with the two nations` laws to avoid double
taxation in the production and sale of minerals.
</P>
<P>
The treaty involves an area that stretches 5,000 kilometers
from the frontier with Bolivia in the North to the Southern Cone
in Argentina`s province of Santa Cruz.
</P>
<P>
The area has a variable width of 15 to 190 kilometers in Chile
and 20 to 220 kilometers in Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
