<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Bone, Tissue Donations Needed in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is campaigning for
more donations of bones and tissues for saving more lives.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Biomaterial Center, which serves as a national bone
and tissue bank, is calling on relatives of accident victims to
donate bones and tissues from the victims for the benefit of
suffering patients.
</P>
<P>
Live bones are vital to victims of bone cancer and those who
lose their bones in accidents.
</P>
<P>
As many as 70 percent of the bereft, especially those who lost
their loved ones in accidents or physical assaults, are against
donating the dead victims' bones and tissues, according to
Yongyuth Vatcharadul, director of the center.
</P>
<P>
Demand for bones of people who die less than 24 hours is
growing, prompting the center to increase its supplies, he was
quoted as saying by the Bangkok Post Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The center, which has been conducting research and development
on related transplanting technology, is turning to medical
doctors, the media and monks to help promote bone and tissue
donations to save others' lives and alleviate their agony.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
