<HEADLINE> Thailand Sees 27 Bln Baht Trade Surplus in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANKOK, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand recorded a trade
surplus of 27.3 billion baht (675 million U.S. dollars) in
November, the third consecutive month it saw a trade surplus this
year.
</P>
<P>
Thai exports reached 181.493 billion baht (4.5 billion dollars)
in value in the month, while Thai import value posted 154.205
billion baht (3.8 billion dollars), according to the latest
statistics from the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Thailand posted its first monthly trade surplus in September,
which was about 5.3 billion baht. It also reported a trade surplus
of 16.40 billion baht in October.
</P>
<P>
However, during the first 11 months of this year, Thailand
still faced a trade deficit of 147.4 billion baht with imports
totaling 1,727.3 billion baht in value.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that the baht plunge contributed to the
export growth in the past months, but it did not give the figures
in dollar terms.
</P>
<P>
The ministry predicted that Thai exports are expected to hit
1,700 billion baht this year, a jump of 21.4 percent from last
year in baht terms.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the ministry said that the country's economic
growth this year is likely to fall to 0.3 percent before it
further drops below minus 0.7 percent next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
