<HEADLINE> Bookstores In Southeastern Chinese City Now Lend Books </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The residents of Fuzhou,
capital of China's Fujian Province, now can not only buy their
books, but also rent them from individually-owned bookstores.
</P>
<P>
A store owner says that the business was harder before because
the prices for books were too expensive for most
customers. However, "The situation got much better when I started
the rental service early last year," he said. Many customers
borrow a number of books when they come shopping in his store.
</P>
<P>
And, after they read the books, many come back and buy some of
them, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lin Qiang, another bookstore owner, says that many students and
teachers visit his store. To provide more and different books
for them, Lin has opened several book sections, like
technology, economics, social sciences, music and the arts. The
large number of books available for borrowing has had a good
reception among readers. 
</P>
