<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is soon to launch a
program to rehabilitate the country's irrigation network, the
official newspaper Daily News said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The government will spend 2.35 billion Rupees (39.2 million
U.S. dollars) to rehabilitate the existing network, carry out a
water project in North Western province and complete the initial
phase of the Mau Ara and Weli Oya river diversion projects in the
South.
</P>
