<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Loan For Coal Railway Arranged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- A loan of 6.2 billion yuan
(747 million U.S.dollars) will be invested in the construction of
a railway to transport coal from West China to the country's
eastern provinces.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Bank of China has signed an agreement to
entrust the China Construction Bank (CCB) to handle the loan for
the construction of the Shuohuang Railway, which will run 599 km
from Shuozhou, Shanxi Province to Huanghua Port of the neighboring
Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Railway Sub-branch of the Beijing
Branch of the CCB will act as the agent responsible for the
issuance of the loan, the supervision of its use, and its final
recall.
</P>
<P>
The 6.2 billion yuan loan carries an interest rate of 10.53
percent and a repayment term of 15 years.
</P>
<P>
The Shuohuang Railway to be double-tracked and electric, is
designed to be capable of transporting 68 million tons of coal
annually. It is expected to be completed by 2003 and total
investment is estimated at 16.6 billion yuan (about two billion
U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Railway is part of the third construction phrase of the
Shenhua Project, which is aimed at building a huge transport
network to carry coal from western to eastern China.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 90 billion yuan (10.8 billion
U.S. dollars), the Shenhua Project is second only to the Three
Gorges Project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
