<HEADLINE> Carvin Withdraws from World Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chad Carvin,
U.S. Swimming's 1997 Swimmer of the Year, has withdrawn from the
world championship team because of a back injury, the U.S.
federation announced in Colorado Spring, Colorado on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Carvin has a bulging disc in his lower back that has bothered
him since before the world championship trials in July,
U.S. Swimming said.
</P>
<P>
The world swimming championships will be held in Perth,
Australia, from January 8-18.
</P>
<P>
Carvin won six U.S. national titles and five international
medals in 1997. In February he won four titles at the national
championships. 
