<HEADLINE> Important Vegetable Processing Base Being Built In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Luxian County in east China's
Shandong Province has earned nearly 20 million US dollars from
vegetable and fruit exports this year.
</P>
<P>
More than a thousand ha. of vegetable-growing farmland and
convenient transportation have helped turn the county into the
province's largest vegetable-processing base.
</P>
<P>
It has exported 20 varieties of frozen vegetables to Japan,
ROK, and Europe this year, and earned 150 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The county plans to develop more vegetable processing lines and
to have an annual production capacity of 30,000 tons of frozen
vegetables and 10,000 tons of fresh-preserved fruits and
vegetables.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to generate 500 million yuan in annual output
value, 50 million yuan in pre-tax profits, and 60 million US
dollars from exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
