<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Edged South Africa 4-3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, December 17 (Xinhua) -- An injury-time goal by
Christian Callejas gave Uruguay a 4-3 win over South Africa in the
last group match at the Confederations' Cup soccer tournament in
Riyadh on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayans, which have already qualified for the
semi-finals, led 3-1 with 25 minutes left but allowed South Africa
back into the game before snatching a late winner.
</P>
<P>
South Africa, which needed to win the match by six clear goals
to get a semi-final place away from the Czech Republic, jumped
ahead in the 11th minute when captain Lucas Radebe headed home.
</P>
<P>
Dario Silva made it 1-1 for Uruguay and Alvaro Recoba added a
second just before half-time. Silva beat the offside trap to
extend Uruguay's lead in the middle of the second-half.
</P>
<P>
South Africa pulled one back through Helman Mkhalele in the
76th minute and then evened the score through Pollen Ndlanya.
</P>
<P>
The African champions' hope for a winner was dashed as Callejas
swerved a fourth into the net in injury time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
