<HEADLINE> ITTF Pro-Tour Grand Finals to Kick Off in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 International Table
Tennis Federation (ITTF) Pro-Tour Grand Finals are to start here
on Thursday, with the tour's top 16 singles players and best eight
doubles pairs vying for the four annual titles.
</P>
<P>
It will be another chance for world men's singles champion and
Swedish veteran Jan-Ove Waldner, 31, to show his sharp shots and
skillful game following his superb performance at the world
championships in Manchester last May.
</P>
<P>
Waldner, ranked third in the world, will face young Chinese Yan
Sen, now ranked 16th, in the men's singles first round.
</P>
<P>
It should be an easy job for world number one and top seed
Kong Linghui from China to beat his opening-round opponent Leung
Chu Yan, ace player of host Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
And it could also be an easy-going game for world singles
runner-up and second seed here Vladimir Samsonov from Belarus as
he takes on world No. 18 and Chinese youngster Ma Lin.
</P>
<P>
China's Olympic champion Liu Guoliang would have to overcome a
shadow over his mind as he meets Werner Schlager from Austria on
Thursday. It will be their first meeting since Liu lost to the
Austrian in October's World Cup.
</P>
<P>
As China's Olympic champion and world number one woman player
Deng Yaping is absent from the Pro-Tour Grand Finals due to her
university studies back in Beijing, her teammate and world number
two, Li Ju, is the top seed for the four-day event.
</P>
<P>
Li is to take on Schopp Jie from Germany, a former member of
the Chinese national team.
</P>
<P>
And China's world runner-up and world number three Wang Nan,
who is second seed here, is to meet another former Chinese
player, Tian-Zorner Jing who now represents Germany.
</P>
<P>
The singles quarter-finals and semi-finals are set for Friday
and Saturday. The Grand Finals finish on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The doubles first-round matches are slated for Friday.
</P>
