<HEADLINE> NZ Records Trade Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, December 18 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand recorded an 8.5
percent fall in its exports in October, Statistics New Zealand
announced in a press release received Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Exports to NZ's five biggest markets, Australia, Japan, the
United States, the United Kingdom and Korea, all dropped in the
month compared with October 1996.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Japan and Korea were also lower in the year ending
October, although NZ's total exports in that year rose 0.6 percent
to 1.586 billion dollars (1 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"The exports trend is now declining by an average of 0.7
percent per month from the high in June 1977 to the October
month," the press release said.  
</P>
