<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Vladimir Smicer scored three
times to lead the Czech Republic's 6-1 victory over the United
Arab Emirates in the Confederations Cup soccer tournament in
Riyadh on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs have got four points and a plus-four goal
difference. Only a six-goal victory by South Africa over Uruguay,
which already have qualified for the semi-finals, in Wednesday's
second game would keep the Czechs from advancing.
</P>
<P>
Emirates defender Hasan Saeed gave the Czechs the lead in the
11th minute, inadvertenly knocking the ball into his own net as he
tried to clear a cross.
</P>
<P>
Pavel Kuka set up Lazio's Pavel Nedved in the 22st minute for
the second and nine minutes later, Smicer cashed in on a defensive
lapse to score for the third.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes before halftime, Nedved dribbled through and
slotted home the fourth.
</P>
<P>
Smicer got his second goal in the 68th minute and completed his
hat-trick three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
The Emirates scored their consolation goal in the 78th minute
when Adnan Al Talyani caught Czech goalkeeper Pavel Srnicek off
his line to clear a ball. 
</P>
