<HEADLINE> Thailand Company Helps Chinese Poor Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 18 (Xinhua) -- A Thailand company will spend
800,000 to one million yuan to help a poor Chinese village shake
off poverty in three years.
</P>
<P>
The Chia Tai Group of Thailand has sent two technicians to
Miaoziwan Village of Puge County, southwest China's Sichuan
Province. Located in a mountain more than 2,000 meters above sea
level, the village has 286 households. Last year, farmers' per
capita income was only 400 yuan.
</P>
<P>
In April, an investigation group from the Thai company visited
the village and decided to start some poverty relief projects,
according to the provincial poverty relief office.
</P>
<P>
Now four projects are already underway. The group has provided
500,000 yuan in interest-free loans to finance a hydropower
station with a capacity of 100 KW, and to help the village develop
chicken and pig raising.
</P>
<P>
The group also aims to help expand the application of
high-yield maize, to improve farmers' houses, and rebuild roads,
the office said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
