<DOCNO> XIE19971218.0354 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Loans for Low-Income Housing in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of two loans
totaling 62 million U.S. dollars equivalent to Ecuador to support
greater access to housing for low-income populations.
</P>
<P>
The project will increase the efficiency and equity of public
investments in the housing sector and promote greater private
sector participation through the modernization of the legal and
institutional framework. A system of direct subsidies for
low-income housing will be established to help finance either
improvement or construction of new units.
</P>
<P>
The program will also promote deepening of the housing credit
market through technical assistance to intermediary financial
institutions and credit technologies designed to benefit housing
for low-income groups.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing consists of a 32 million dollars loan from
the Bank's ordinary capital and a second loan of 30 million
dollars in local currency from the Fund for Special Operations.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is about 68.6 million dollars.
Apart from the IDB loans, local counterpart funds total 6.6
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
