<HEADLINE> Canadian Banks Raise Mortgage Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Canada's commercial banks
raised their mortgage rates by 0.30 of a percentage point today,
which will go into effect tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
This was the third time in less than a month that the banks
increased their mortgage rates.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce led the pack today by
announcing a rate hike of 0.30 percentage point on terms from six
months to three years.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the six-month open rate goes up to 6.50 percent
and three-year to 7.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Its four-year rate rose by 0.20 percentage point to 7.05
percent, while longer-term rates remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The move was quickly followed by the Royal Bank, the Bank of
Montreal and other commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
Despite the recent rate increases, Canada's mortgage rates are
still quite low compared with few years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
