<HEADLINE> Botswana's Army Chief to Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Commander of the
Botswana Defense Force (BDF), Seretse Khama Ian Khama has
announced that he would retire on March 31 next year, South
African Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
His retirement will be on the same day as that of President
Ketumile Masire.
</P>
<P>
The announcement has given rise to fresh speculation that he
may seek to enter politics. But BDF spokesman Mogorosi Baatweng
said today that Khama has not come to a decision.
</P>
<P>
"He said he would make up his mind at the right time."
</P>
<P>
Khama has been criticized for recent purchases of arms for the
BDF. He has always responded that the BDF was behind in the
development of its infrastructure and training. 
</P>
